<p>Why do I have to provide the leading backslash when providing the path to a class? [\Zend\Validator\EmailAddress() and not just Zend\Validator\EmailAddress()]</p>  <blockquote>   <p>$validator = new \Zend\Validator\EmailAddress();</p>      <p>$email = "example@example.com";</p>      <p>if ($validator->isValid($email)) {      // email appears to be valid   } else {      // email is invalid; print the reasons      foreach ($validator->getMessages() as $messageId => $message) {          echo "Validation failure '$messageId': $message\n";      }   }</p> </blockquote>  <p>Thanks!</p>